The paper deals with the observability problem in a linear system, which is a topic in control theory (cs.SY). The sparsity constraint is a common theme in signal processing and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of randomized matrices, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The sufficient conditions obtained for observability involve linear algebraic techniques, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper deals with the recovery of the initial state, which is a problem in data science and optimization (cs.DS).
